<h1>Find</h1>
<p>
  The Find dialog searches the model by name.
</p>

<p>To search an model from within Vergil, select Graph -&gt; Find.</p>
</p>

<p>The 
  <a href="ptdoc:ptolemy.vergil.basic.SearchResultDialog">SearchResultsDialog</a>
  has the following checkboxes:</p>
<dl>
  <dt>Include Values</dt>
  <dd>Search the values of Settable objects</dd>

  <dt>Include Names</dt>
  <dd>Search the names of objects</dd>

  <dt>Recursive Search</dt>
  <dd>Search within the objects immediately contained</dd>
  
  <dt>Case Sensitive</dt>
  <dd>Match the case</dd>
</dl>

<p>After clicking on the Search button, the matches (if any), are
listed.  To highlight the object or container of the object, select
the name of the object in the list.  To open the container of the
object, double click on the name of the object in the list.
</p>
				  
